org.openmuc.jdlms.datatypes

Class DataObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openmuc.jdlms.datatypes.DataObject

  • public class DataObject
extends java.lang.Object
    Container class holding data about to send to the smart meter or received by the smart meter

    Either stores a Number, List of DataObjects, a byte array, BitString or a subtype CosemDateFormat.

      • isComplex

        public boolean isComplex()
        Checks if the data of this container is of a complex type.

        A complex container holds one or more sub container of type DataObject as values.

        A container is of complex type if getType() returns either DataObject.Type.ARRAY, DataObject.Type.STRUCTURE or DataObject.Type.COMPACT_ARRAY.

        Returns:
        true is the DataObject holds a List of DataObject.

      • isByteArray

        public boolean isByteArray()
        Checks if the data of this container is a byte array.

        A container is a byte array if getType() returns either DataObject.Type.OCTET_STRING, DataObject.Type.VISIBLE_STRING, DataObject.Type.BIT_STRING or DataObject.Type.UTF8_STRING.

        Returns:
        true if the data is a byte array (byte[]).
